title: Mapping cylinder
type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki

The //mapping cylinder// $$M_f$$ of a map $$f\colon X \to Y$$ is the quotient of $$(X \times I) \sqcup Y$$ by the equivalence relation generated by $$(x,1) \sim f(x).$$ If $$Y = \{*\}$$ is a singleton, then $$M_f \eqqcolon C(X)$$ is the //cone// over $$X.$$